Package: linkinfer
Title: Methods for Inference with Linked Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Casey F.", "Breen", email = "casey.breen@austin.utexas.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Won-tak", "Joo", email = "wjoo@ufl.edu",
           role = "aut")
  )
Description: Tools for diagnosing and correcting bias arising from record
    linkage errors. Provides methods for comparing linked samples to
    reference populations, adjusting for missed matches using inverse
    probability weighting, post-stratification, and raking, and validating
    adjustments using validation variables. Companion package to Breen and
    Joo (2026) "Population Research With Linked Data: Methods for
    Inference".
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
